  <rte>
    <name>Fleetwith Pike and Haystacks from Gatescarth</name>
    <desc>This is a relatively short Lake District horseshoe walk starting from Gatescarth at the foot of Honister Pass on the Buttermere side. Despite being short in distance, the route offers an outstanding view of Lakeland scenery including many of the high fells and some its lakes.</desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1289-description</url>
